{
  "stem": "22586.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Tere. ?] Masaryk was the president of Czechoslovakia and the main-- main square in town was named after him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was like a plaza.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Tere ?] means plaza.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the street I lived on was sort of a continuation of the Masaryk [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Tere, ?] of the main plaza.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was a park there with a statue of the president, Masaryk.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And our-- my elementary school was right around the, the same plaza that I went to.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And next door to us was a nunnery.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was one of our preoccupations was [INAUDIBLE] to always go spy on the nuns.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He had a wine cellar, and he sold mainly wholesale.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But a lot of Jewish-- on Fridays, a lot of Jewish people came to buy wine from him just for Fridays, because it had to be bought from a Jewish person.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Once a non-Jewish person touched a wine, it was no longer kosher.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So a lot of Jewish people came on Fridays.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But mainly, he sold wholesale to inns and-- I guess mainly for inns.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he would-- he would have-- he had a wine cellar.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The wine was kept in huge barrels.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember in, in the summer, or rather, in the fall, they would harvest the grape, and they would-- he would-- he would make the wine out of it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I very fondly remember having the new wine before it fermented.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we'd go roast potatoes in the skin and have the-- this new wine with it, which was delicious.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We spoke Hungarian, because my father mainly spoken Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So in the house, actually, at home we spoke mainly Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Czech was spoken in school and, and Hungarian at home.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
